==English==
===Verb===
'''[[lay]] [[a]] [[foundation]]''' (''past'': '''[[laid]] a foundation''') (''present'': '''[[laying]] a foundation''') (''future'': '''[[will]] lay a foundation''')
# (''law''): [[elicit]] [[information]] from a [[witness]] to show that the witness has [[knowledge]] of a matter before the witness testifies to the matter itself
#:In order to '''lay a foundation''' for the witness to describe the murder, the prosecutor first had to show that the witness was present when the murder occured.

